{
  "texts": [
    "Medium level might include examples such as personalised or contextbased assessments (e.g.",
    "asking students to write to a particular audience whose knowledge and values must be considered or asking questions that would require them to give a response that draws from concepts that were learnt in class, in a lab, field trip… etc).",
    "In contrast, hard assessments include projects involving realworld applications, synchronous oral assessments, or panel assessments (University of Cape Town, 2023).",
    "4-tier-systems are analogues.",
    "The only difference is that they break down the \"middle ground\"."
  ]
}